  "metadata": {
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Doing advanced optimization to further reduce your app’s size"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Following the basic optimizations described in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.Xcode/documentation/Xcode/doing-basic-optimization-to-reduce-your-app-s-size",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "is a good way to decrease the size of your app. However, you can optimize your app’s",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "size further to minimize its footprint on a device and provide a fast download, installation,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and update experience.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "doing-advanced-optimization-to-further-reduce-your-app-s-size-1",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Optimize-your-apps-asset-files",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Optimize your app’s asset files",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Assets often make up a large portion of an app. Consider the following optimizations:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Use the most efficient image and video format possible.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "strong"
            },
            {
              "text": " Image and video assets",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "are common contributors to large app sizes. Using a more efficient image file format",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "is a good way to reduce your app’s size. For example, consider using the HEIF format",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for images, and the HEVC format for videos. If you’re using PNG files, consider using",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "8-bit instead of 32-bit PNGs. Doing so can decrease the image size to a quarter of",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the original size.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Compress images.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "strong"
            },
            {
              "text": " For 32-bit images, using ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://www.adobe.com/photoshop",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": "’s",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "“Save for Web” feature can reduce the size of JPEG and PNG images considerably.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Compress audio files.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "strong"
            },
            {
              "text": " As a general rule, compress audio using ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "AAC",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "MP3",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "codecs, and experiment with a reduced bit rate. Quite often, a 44.1 kHz sample rate",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "isn’t necessary, and a lower bit rate clip won’t result in a perceptible drop in",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "quality. Learn more about optimizing your audio assets by watching ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/wwdc/2011/?id=404",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Reduce-the-size-of-app-updates",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Reduce the size of app updates",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Instead of always downloading the whole app when an update to the app is available,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the App Store creates an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "update package",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": ". It compares one or more prior versions",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "of your app to the new version and creates an optimized package. This package contains",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "only the content that has changed between versions of your app, excluding any content",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that didn’t change.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "This comparison looks at everything in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "application bundle",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": ", including the application",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "executable, storyboards, nibs, localizations, and other assets, like images.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Consider the following to reduce the size of your app’s update package:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Don’t make unnecessary modifications to files. Compare the contents of the prior",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "and new versions of your app with ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "diff",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " or another directory comparison tool, and",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "verify that it doesn’t contain any unexpected changes.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Store content that you expect to change in an update in separate files from content",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "that you don’t expect to change.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Don’t rely on the creation and modification dates of files in your application",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "bundle. The operating system updates your app using the update package, and updates",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "files only if their content changes. It doesn’t update files because of changes to",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "metadata; for example, the creation and modification dates.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Adopt-on-demand-resources",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Adopt on-demand resources",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Analyze all of your app’s assets and determine which resources it uses infrequently.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Group the infrequently used resources into ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "asset packs",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": ". When you upload your app",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to App Store Connect, asset packs don’t become part of your app’s initial download",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or app updates. Instead, the app can download them separately as needed. See the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/FileManagement/Conceptual/On_Demand_Resources_Guide/index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015083",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for more information.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you can’t adopt on-demand resources, consider implementing a web service that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "provides them, and download them in the background as needed, using ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/urlsession",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "To learn more, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/url_loading_system/downloading_files_in_the_background",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Leverage-app-thinning",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Leverage app thinning",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "App thinning",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " is a technology that ensures that an app’s IPA file only contains",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "resources and code that’s necessary to run the app on a particular device. Apps that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "are available in the App Store, and that you distribute to testers using TestFlight,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "already leverage app thinning. However, if you distribute an in-house enterprise",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "app, or distribute your builds to testers without using TestFlight, you must enable",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "app thinning when you export your app. To use app thinning:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Archive your app in Xcode.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Select the archived app in the organizer window, and click Distribute App.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Export your app using Xcode, and choose “All compatible device variants” for app",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "thinning in the export sheet. If you support only a limited number of devices in",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "your app, select the ones that apply.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To learn more about app thinning, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://help.apple.com/xcode/mac/11.0/index.html?localePath=en.lproj#/devde46df08a",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and watch ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2015/404/",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
